\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator of the representation considered the initial evaluators\'27 reports and the additional information submitted by the institution. Although the institution seems to have paid attention to the re-curriculation of the programme after the initial submission\'2C the evaluator felt that there are still areas that need attention.  The evaluator noted a sense that the institution simply tried to enhance the 240-credit Diploma\'3A Executive Secretarial Studies qualification they currently offer\'2C without taking into consideration that the new qualification shouldn\'E2\'80\'99t simply have more credits built into it\'2C but also an understanding of a broader range of topics in this field\'2C as well as enhanced opportunity for articulation onto other programmes.  This is not currently the case for Business-related qualifications due to the lack of such modules on the current curriculum \'E2\'80\'93 this is in stark contrast to the statement of the institution regarding the possibility of articulation into a Diploma in Business Management or a B Com degree.  It is thus concluded that the programme design is still deficient in terms of the following\'3A\line \'E2\'80\'A2 A Business Management module should be considered in the first year to give students an orientation into the Business world\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Entrepreneurship is offered in first year\'2C before general management concepts are covered \'28as above\'29.  This seems the wrong way round.  Students will battle to grasp some of the concepts if they have not been introduced to it before.\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Human Resources Management should be offered at first and second year level to serve as pre-requisites for Organisational Behaviour.  \line \'E2\'80\'A2 An inclusion of the Financial\'2FBookkeeping element will enhance the incumbents\'E2\'80\'99 job and entrepreneurial prospects.\line \line The institution has re-submitted a list of staff members and their qualifications and experience.  All are acceptable for purpose of the offering of this programme.\line \line While the evaluator recommends provisional accreditation with conditions\'2C the Directorate is concerned that the design is insufficiently coherent. The current name is also problematic. \line \cell \pard 

